#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
GitLab Epic Migration Validator + Board Mirror + Rollback
AIR-GAPPED / STDLIB-ONLY edition   |   SBIePay  epay -> itepaypg-sbiepay2

WHAT THIS DOES
  * Validates epic migration integrity (counts, hierarchy, drift, orphans).
  * Mirrors EPIC BOARDS from source to target with full fidelity:
      board name, hide_backlog_list, hide_closed_list, board label scope,
      and every label-based list in the correct position.
  * Every write is recorded to a ROLLBACK JOURNAL so it can be fully undone.
  * --rollback reverses ONLY what this script created on the TARGET. Nothing else.

WORKS ON EPICS / EPIC BOARDS ONLY. It never touches code, MRs, issues,
pipelines, members, or settings.

NO pip packages required. Pure standard library (urllib/json/csv/ssl/argparse).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
READ vs WRITE — exactly what happens at each stage
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  STAGE                         OPERATION    TARGET IMPACT
  1 version check               READ         none
  2 group enumeration           READ         none
  3 epic compare (counts/etc)   READ         none
  4 board compare               READ         none
  5 board mirror (only if asked):
      - create board            WRITE        adds a NEW epic board on target
      - set board label scope   WRITE        on the NEW board only
      - create board list       WRITE        on the NEW board only
    (each write is journaled for rollback; existing boards are NEVER modified)
  6 csv reports                 LOCAL write  files on your machine only
  ROLLBACK MODE (--rollback):
      - destroy created lists   WRITE        removes lists this script created
      - destroy created boards  WRITE        removes boards this script created
    (reads the journal; touches only IDs the journal recorded)

DEFAULT MODE IS READ-ONLY. Writes happen only with explicit flags.

USAGE
  python epics_Validation.py                          # validate only (READ ONLY)
  python epics_Validation.py --mirror-boards          # DRY RUN: show planned writes
  python epics_Validation.py --mirror-boards --apply  # perform board mirror (WRITE)
  python epics_Validation.py --rollback               # DRY RUN: show planned undo
  python epics_Validation.py --rollback --apply       # undo last mirror (WRITE)
  python epics_Validation.py --rollback --journal <path.jsonl> --apply
"""

